1
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja, vê heftiyê jî em derbasî gundê Şêx
bûn.
 
Yes dear viewers, this week too we passed by the village of
Şêx.

2
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Ev gundê Şêx girêdayî navçeya Raco ye.
 
This village of Şêx is connected to the district of Raco.

3
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Ê destpêkê vê gundê ava kirî, Şêx Ehmed bû.
 
The first to build this village was Şêx Ehmed.

4
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Ji Kobanê berê xwe da Efrînê, hat li vir gundek ava kir,
niha gundekî mezin jê çêbûye.
 
He headed from Kobanê to Efrîn, came and built a village
here, now a big village has come of it.

5
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Niha em ê derbasî gund bibin, em ê bi hev re gundê Şêx nas
bikin.
 
Now we will enter the village, we will get to know the
village of Şêx together.

6
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Me xwest em gundê Şêx hinekî nas bikin. Ev gundê Şêx çend
sal e çêbûye?
 
We wanted to get to know the village of Şêx a bit. How many
years has this village of Şêx been built?

7
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Ehlensehlen. Gundê Şêx emrê xwe teqrîben sêsed sal heye.
 
Welcome. The village of Şêx's age is approximately three
hundred years.

8
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Yanî çend sal kêmtir, zêdetir, dor sêsed sal e.
 
That is, a few years less, more, around three hundred years.

9
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Ji berê de gund li vir e, yan li gundekî din bû?
 
Has the village been here from the beginning, or was it in
another village?

10
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Berê bidayet da, hê nehatî vê gundî yekî şên bike, li vê
sirtê jor xaniyê xwe girt.
 
Before in the beginning, before coming to populate this
village, he built his house on this upper ridge.

11
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Çend meh tê de derbas bû zivistan hat, sermayek rabû,
mirîşkên wî ji sermayê mirin.
 
A few months passed in it, winter came, a cold arose, his
chickens died from the cold.

12
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Pêşî ji ber sermayê ji wura reviyan, berê ev der çal bû.
 
First they fled from there because of the cold, before this
place was a pit.

13
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Çal bû, kelem bû, fe da ket jêr, vê mewqeyê noka em lê, li
vê derê, xaniyê xwe girt. Vê sirtê berda, da ket jêr.
 
It was a pit, it was a stump, so he went down, this location
we are at now, here, he built his house. He left this ridge,
went down.

14
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Ji vura çiqas dûr e ew?
 
How far is that from here?

15
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Ji vir desed metir e, sêsed metir e. Serî, serî vê telê.
 
From here it is two hundred meters, three hundred meters.
The top, the top of this hill.

16
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Nexwe ê destpêkê derbasî vir bû Şêx Ehmed bû? Ew ji ku derê,
ji Kobanê hat?
 
So the first to cross here was Şêx Ehmed? Where did he come
from, from Kobanê?

17
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Şêx Ehmed bû, ji Kobanê, ji Taşlûkê hat.
 
It was Şêx Ehmed, from Kobanê, he came from Taşlûk.

18
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Wekî, berê bav û kalên me yê mezin digotin me, ji Taşlûkê
hat vê derê.
 
As, before our big ancestors used to tell us, he came from
Taşlûk to here.

19
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Destpêkê hat li Birnêşê, ji wî gundî?
 
Initially he came to Birnêş, from that village?

20
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Bidayet da hê nehatî, eza bû, hat bi tenê, çend salan li
gundê dî, Birnêş, rûnişt.
 
In the beginning before coming, he was single, he came
alone, he stayed for a few years in the other village,
Birnêş.

21
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Be'dê çend salan li wir zewicî, xwest, go ez ê bi tenê xwe
rûnim. Fe hat vê mewqeyê îxtiyar kir û şên kir.
 
After a few years he married there, he wanted, he said I
will settle alone. So he came to this location, chose it and
populated it.

22
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Gundê din jî ew jî gelek nêzîk e, ew jî cîranên we ne?
 
The other village is also very close, are they also your
neighbors?

23
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Nêzîk e tiştekî kêm e, sê kîlometir ji me dûr in.
 
It is close it is a little thing, they are three kilometers
away from us.

24
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Ji wî gundî zewicî?
 
He married from that village?

25
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Na ji gundekî din zewicî.
 
No he married from another village.

26
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Û be'dî zewicî, hat, go ew ê bi tenê xwe rûne, hat vê derê
îxtiyar kir.
 
And after he married, he came, he said he will settle alone,
he came here and chose it.

27
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Û, ew gundê me vê derê girt û xaniyê xwe girt û gund şên kir
û mewqeyê xwe jî vê derê vir di navbera du çiyayî hewar e.
 
And, he took our village here and built his house and
populated the village and its location is also here between
two mountains it's flatland.

28
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Yanî gundê me, gundê çiyê, gundê dî, evana di Çiyayê Hawarê
de ne. Me'rûf in.
 
That is our village, the mountain village, the other
village, these are in the Hawar Mountain. They are well-
known.

29
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Û Şêx, bi xwe însanekî şêx bû û şêxekî koklî, wek dibêjin.
 
And Şêx, he himself was a sheikh person and a deeply rooted
sheikh, as they say.

30
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Yanî di mentiqeyê de gişkî de em me'rûf in bi şêxitiya xwe.
 
I mean in the entire region we are all known for our
sheikhhood.

31
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:40,000
Kerametek xwe... yanî heta gund jî gundên dûr jî qîmetekî
didanê, teqdîrekî dikirin.
 
His miracle... I mean even the village, the distant villages
also gave a value to him, gave an appreciation.

32
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:49,000
Xêrekî, sirekî xwe hebû, kerametekî xwe hebû. Mişkelek
hebûya bi xwe, bi şeklekî tew'î, dihatin, diçûn, meselan
digotin em ê vê mişkeleyê hel bikin.
 
He had a blessing, a secret, he had a miracle. If there was
a problem, voluntarily, coming, going, for example they used
to say we will solve this problem.

33
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Milet nedikarî bêjin na, nedikarîn, êdî ne dihatin bêjin na.
 
The people couldn't say no, they couldn't, anymore they
couldn't come to say no.

34
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Boy wê tiştî jî qîmetê xwe di mentiqeyê de zêde dibû.
 
For that thing too his value in the region was increasing.

35
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,000
Teqdîrekî didanê digotin wella ew Şêxler e nabe.
 
They gave an appreciation saying by God they are the Sheikhs
it doesn't suit us.

36
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:03,000
Tab'en berî hukmet deret kêm bûn, yanî çûn hatin hevdû gilî
kirin, ev hukmetên derve û tişt nebûn.
 
Of course before the government appeared they were few, I
mean going coming complaining about each other, these
outside governments and things didn't exist.

37
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:09,000
Ê zêde yan eger biçûna cem Şêxleran yan cem axan meselan
mişkeleyên xwe hel dikirin.
 
And mostly either if they went to the Sheikhs or to the
aghas for example they solved their problems.

38
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Şêxleran jî bi hukmê wê yekê 'elaqeta xwe bi miletî re
dihatin û bi şeklekî silmî çareser dikirin, hel dikirin.
 
The Sheikhs also by the rule of that one their relationship
with the people they came and in a peaceful way they solved,
resolved.

39
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Ê piştî Şêx Ehmed di gund de kî mezinê wan bû? Rihspiyê wan
kî bû?
 
And after Şêx Ehmed who was their elder in the village? Who
was their white-bearded elder?

40
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:34,000
Tab'en Şêx Ehmed, dawîn zewicî sê çar qîzên xwe bûn, dan
mêr, lê piştî ku emr jî pir bû, mezin bû, yanî berî mirinê
lawkî xwe çêbû.
 
Of course Şêx Ehmed, lastly married he had three four
daughters, he gave them to husbands, but after his age
became a lot too, he grew old, I mean before dying he had a
son.

41
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Rabû wê lawkî jî bi bavkê xwe nav kirin. Navê wî jî nav lê
nan Şêx Ehmed.
 
He got up and named that boy too after his father. His name
too they named Şêx Ehmed.

42
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Ê diya, rabû Şêx Ehmedê diduyan, zewicî, pênc lawên xwe jî
bûn.
 
So, the second Şêx Ehmed got up, married, he also had five
sons.

43
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Tab'en ê mezin, sê çar, meselan wek dibêjin qedir didan wî.
 
Of course the older one, three four, for example as they say
gave respect to him.

44
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Diyar e kî mezin ba meselan kî ew bû.
 
It is clear whoever was older for example who it was him.

45
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Wek dibêjin, maf derketa, rê didan wî, meselan wek dibêjin,
ew dikirin didîtin.
 
As they say, if a right emerged, they gave way to him, for
example as they say, they did they saw.

46
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:06,000
Pê cema'etan, deran ve mişkeleyan wisa bû.
 
Through assemblies, outside doors problems it was like that.

47
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:15,000
Mezinan jî wê wextê dî, wextê, tê de kî mezin bû, ew dihat û
milet diket dorê, hel dikirin.
 
The elders too that other time, the time, in it whoever was
older, he came and the people gathered around him, they
solved it.

48
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,000
Gund jî hemû malbat e?
 
Is the village too all family?

49
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Em gişt ji, ji koka Şêx Ehmed a Silef de ne. Di gundî de em
gişt in. Kese xerîb tê de tune ye. Gişt 'aîle yek e.
 
We all are from, from the root of Şêx Ehmed the Predecessor.
We all are in the village. There is no stranger in it. The
whole family is one.

50
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Ne wek, derve da, dibêjin "Ema yek dibêje ez ji gundê Şêx
me", malbat jî hene. Lê giştî wek dibêjin?
 
Not like, outside, they say "But one says I am from the
village of Şêx", there are families too. But overall as they
say?

51
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:36,000
Malbat, te dît pirs, gundê me, bi navê malbatek, yanî encam
de yek e, yek malbat e. Piştre tê de malbatî yanî...
 
Family, you saw the question, our village, by the name of a
family, I mean in the end it is one, it is one family.
Afterwards there are families in it I mean...

52
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Malbata piştî Şêx Ehmedê diduyan pênc lawên xwe bûn, ew jî
zewicîn, qeçkên wan jî bûn.
 
The family after the second Şêx Ehmed had five sons, they
too married, their children too were born.

53
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:56,000
Niha li gund meselan dibêjin Mala Ebdî Seydo, dibêjin Mala
Şêx Ehmed, dibêjin Mala Zilfê, dibêjin Mala Kolê, Mala Êhû,
Mala Salihê, Mala Memî Eçmê.
 
Now in the village for example they say Ebdî Seydo's House,
they say Şêx Ehmed's House, they say Zilfê's House, they say
Kolê's House, Êhû's House, Salihê's House, Memî Eçmê's
House.

54
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Ha ev ne di gundan de û tab'en em gişt jî ji bavekî de ne,
em ji Şêx Ehmed in, Şêx Ehmed Silef.
 
Ha these are they in the villages and of course we all too
are from one father, we are from Şêx Ehmed, Şêx Ehmed the
Predecessor.

55
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,000
Mamoste Mihemed niha di gundî de çiqas mal e?
 
Teacher Mihemed now in the village how many houses are
there?

56
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:13,000
Niha di gundî de dor çil malî heye.
 
Now in the village there are around forty houses.

57
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:17,000
Bes ên derveyî gund ve, dor sed û pêncî malî heye.
 
But those outside of the village, there are around a hundred
and fifty houses.

58
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Li kuderê rûniştin e ewna?
 
Where are they settled?

59
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Ewna berî van ehdasan e pir li Heleb û li Efrînê bûn.
 
They before these events mostly were in Aleppo and in Efrîn.

60
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:27,000
Û gund jî wek sê malî, di van ehdasan de wek deha malî lê
zêde bûn.
 
And the village too like three houses, in these events like
ten more houses were added to it.

61
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
Yanî hêna dijîn li Efrînê ewna bi piranî?
 
I mean they still live in Efrîn mostly?

62
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,000
Li Efrînê ne, tab'en Heleb kes neman.
 
They are in Efrîn, of course Aleppo no one remained.

63
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Li Efrînê ne û pir jî niha li Tirkiyeyê ne û hen jî çûne
derve jî.
 
They are in Efrîn and many too now are in Turkey and some
too have gone abroad as well.

64
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:40,000
Derve jî yanî li hemû dewletan hene.
 
Abroad too I mean they are in all countries.

65
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:53,000
Meselan wek em dibêjin li Almanyayê hene, li Danîmark hene,
Swêd hene, Fînlenda hene, evana berî ehdasan de gihîştin,
Fînlenda, Nerwêc. Danîmark van dewletan gihîşt, ku noka xwa
gundin.
 
For example as we say they are in Germany, in Denmark they
are, Sweden they are, Finland they are, these before the
events arrived, Finland, Norway. Denmark they reached these
countries, that now they themselves are a village.

66
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Mamoste Mihemed hûn û devera xwe, Kobanê de hûn diçin tên?
 
Teacher Mihemed you and your region, in Kobanê do you go
come?

67
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Kobanê... pêşî ez bawer nakim em hevdû bi xwe nas dikir...
yanî.
 
Kobanê... first I don't believe we ourselves knew each
other... I mean.

68
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,000
Lê piştî van ehdasan bi wek çend salan vê ber xwe da de...
bi navên hev nas bûn... em çûn dîtin hatin, çêbûn.
 
But after these events by like a few years we brought
towards ourselves... by names of each other we were known...
we went seeing coming, they happened.

69
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Em dehrin tên, yanî munasabetan em diçûn û ewana dihatin.
 
We go come, I mean on occasions we went and they came.

70
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:15,000
Mêriya, ew carekî Ebdullah Gelo, pismamê me çû hecê an
wefdekî em ji vê derê çûn, em çûn pîroz kir ji wan re.
 
Relatives, that one time Ebdullah Gelo, our cousin went to
Hajj or a delegation we went from here, we went and
congratulated them.

71
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Yanî çûn û hatin van fetreya paşî çêbû. Berî van ehdasan da
em diçûn dehatin.
 
I mean going and coming happened in this last period. Before
these events we were going and coming.

72
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:28,000
Ê wek, gundê we niha, gundê Şêx hûn debara xwe bi çi dikin?
Hûn jiyana xwe bi çi derbas dikin?
 
And like, your village now, the village of Şêx how do you
make your living? What do you spend your life with?

73
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:32,000
Wella niha debara piraniya li ser zeytûnê ye.
 
Well now the living mostly is on olives.

74
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:38,000
Û hena pez xwedî dikin. Yanî wek pênc şeş malan jî pez xwedî
dikin, pê debara xwe dikin.
 
And some raise sheep. I mean like five six houses also raise
sheep, with it they make their living.

75
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Yanî gund mezin nabe bi îtîbarê... kuderê... cihek tunebû
wisa mecbûr dibûn derdiketin diçûn Heleb wek karker... bi
xebatê... wate debarê xwe dabîn dikirin.
 
I mean the village doesn't get big due to the... where...
there was no place so they were forced to go out to Aleppo
as laborers... with work... meaning they provided their
living.

76
00:09:50,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Pir ekseriya naha, elhemdulîllah milk girtine, heta derveyî
sînorê gund dî, gund de... meselen wek li Deştê... li cema
Êbrazê... li vir na... li Qitîşê...
 
Most majority now, thank God they took property, even
outside the other border of the village, in the village...
for example like in Deşt... near Êbraz... here no... in
Qitîş...

77
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:06,000
...balkêş û xweşik e. Gundê re, pê diheşîne. Û pirkî zeytûn
e.
 
...interesting and beautiful. To the village, it gives
greenness. And there are many olives.

78
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Mamoste Mihemed, em dixwazin dawiyê da te tiştekî ji bo
Kobanê bêjî.
 
Teacher Mihemed, we want you to say something about Kobani
at the end.

79
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:26,000
Welle bi îtîbar ev, yanî pêşerojê ji Kobanê re, em
berxwedana Kobanê jî pîroz dikin, û em wek dibê... em jî bi
aliyê xwe re, çi ji me tê xwestin em dîsa amade ne ji vê
re... biqedînin yanî.
 
Well, by consideration, that is, for the future of Kobani,
we also congratulate the resistance of Kobani, and as we
say... we also from our side, whatever is asked of us we are
again ready for it... to fulfill it.

80
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Mala we ava be.
 
Thank you.

81
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Wê te jî ava be, ehlen we sehlen. Ser çava.
 
Thank you too, welcome. Upon my eyes.

82
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Tu jî her bijî, spasiyê dikim.
 
May you live long too, thank you.

83
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:45,000
Li rojavayê gund çiyayê Hawarê û gundê Çiyê dikeve.
 
To the west of the village lies Mount Hawar and the village
of Chiya.

84
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:52,000
Li bakur çiyayê Tizbiyê, gundê Qêsim û gundê Goliyan, li
başûr jî çiyayê Dozelkê ye.
 
To the north is Mount Tizbi, the village of Qesim and the
village of Goliyan, to the south is Mount Dozelke.

85
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Gundê Şêx bi kaniyên û newalên xwe navdar e, û gelek gelî û
newal li derdora gund hene.
 
The village of Şêx is famous for its springs and valleys,
and there are many valleys and ravines around the village.

86
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:07,000
Geliyê Gerê li başûrê gund e. Geliyê Dibirk li başûr rojava,
û geliyê Gura li rojhilat e.
 
The Gere Valley is in the south of the village. The Dibirk
Valley is in the southwest, and the Gura Valley is in the
east.

87
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:23,000
Ziyaretgehek bi navê Sebêbiçûk li rojhilatê gund e, xelkê
gund ji bo nexweşiyan û pêkanîna miradan wan serdana vê
ziyaretgehê dikin.
 
A shrine named Sebebicuk is in the east of the village, the
village people visit this shrine for illnesses and
fulfilling their wishes.

88
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Ta niha têkiliya xelkê gund bi xizmiyên wan re yên li
Kobanê, li gundê Daşlo û Mendikê berdewam in û her dem çûn û
hatina navber a wan da heye.
 
Until now, the relationship of the village people with their
relatives in Kobani, in the villages of Dashlo and Mendik,
continues and there is always coming and going between them.

89
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:39,000
Hêş malbat li gund hene û bingeha hemî malbatan yek malbat
e.
 
There are eight families in the village and the origin of
all families is one family.

90
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:48,000
Gundê Şêx gundekî biçûk e, û mezin nebûye, lewma tenê
derdora çil xanî û nêzî sêsed kes li gund jiyan dikin.
 
The village of Şêx is a small village, and it hasn't grown,
therefore only around forty houses and nearly three hundred
people live in the village.

91
00:11:48,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Şêniyên gund debara jiyana xwe bi çandiniyê dikin. Çandinî û
xizmetkirina darên zeytûnê berhema sereke ye, herweha darên
fêkiyan jî diçînin.
 
The inhabitants of the village make their living by farming.
Planting and taking care of olive trees is the main product,
they also plant fruit trees.

92
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Digel çandiniyê hin xelkê gund sewalkariyê jî dikin, û
berhemên wan li bazarên Raco û Efrînê difroşin.
 
Besides farming, some of the village people also do animal
husbandry, and they sell their products in the markets of
Rajo and Afrin.

93
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,000
Rojbaş wer a!
 
Good day to you!

94
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,000
Rojbaş, merheba weşwaro, ehlen we sehlen.
 
Good day, hello to you too, welcome.

95
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,000
Merheba, gelkî merheba!
 
Hello, a big hello!

96
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,000
Merheba. Xweş hatî, ser çava hatî.
 
Hello. Welcome, you came upon my eyes.

97
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:34,000
Xweşbêj wer a. Em ê nas bikin. Ji kerema xwe bidin nasandin.
 
Good words to you. We will get to know you. Please introduce
yourself.

98
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:41,000
Navê min Yûsif e, ez ji gundê Şêx im. Eraza berî min, marê
dikim. Tiştê tu tê, tu marê dikî.
 
My name is Yûsif, I'm from the village of Şêx. This is my
land in front of me, I am tilling it. If you come, you'll
till it.

99
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,000
Kî kê re... em te jî nas bikin.
 
Who with who... let's get to know you too.

100
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:47,000
Şêx Ehmed. Kurê Salih ê ji gundê Şêx e.
 
Şêx Ehmed. Son of Salih from the village of Şêx.

101
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Ser çavên me. Em niha marê dikin.
 
Upon our eyes. We are tilling right now.

102
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,000
Eh wek e wexta xwa ye.
 
Yes, it is its time.

103
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,000
Dema marê ye.
 
It is tilling time.

104
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,000
Ka kerem ke te em... we got...
 
Please, you us... you said...

105
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:09,000
Dema marê ye, dema cût e, îşta alîkariyê. Bi recberiyê...
 
It is tilling time, it is plowing time, here is helping out.
With farming...

106
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Em vî karî naka dikin. Karê... işta marê, cût e, recberî...
 
We are doing this work right now. The work of... tilling,
plowing, farming...

107
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
Te behsa daran kir, we nav dida...
 
You mentioned the trees, you were naming them...

108
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:28,000
Erê, waxta vedana daraye. Ev darên weda dikin iştê mar
dikin, em dajon, karê me ev e.
 
Yes, it is the time of clearing the roots of the trees.
These trees we are clearing their roots, we are tilling
them, we plow them, this is our work.

109
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:31,000
Ê hûn hev rê cîranin jî? Alîkar dibin, bera...
 
And you are neighbors to each other too? You help out, let's
see...

110
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:35,000
Em bav û diran... iştê marê dikim... bav û dirê em cût
dajon, bav û dirê em karo dikin.
 
We are uncle and nephew... we are tilling... uncle and
nephew we are plowing, uncle and nephew we do the work.

111
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:40,000
Eva tiştî xweş e. Mirox di gel yekdu bav û birayê xwe wekî
evan tiştî bê... hev re kar bike, baş e.
 
This is a nice thing. When a person is with one another,
their uncle and brother, like these things... working
together, it's good.

112
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:49,000
Gelekî baş e. Û ewî jî ehlen we sehlen iştê ev karê me ye.
Em gundê piroka we hevdin e, em kurd in. Û iştê... xwedê ev
karê daye me.
 
It is very good. And that too, welcome, here is our work. We
in the village of Pirok are together, we are Kurds. And
here... God has given us this work.

113
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Başqa ji vî karî tenê naha...
 
Other than this work, only now...

114
00:13:52,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Li gund niha tenê ev e, ber pez e. Û marê, û cût e, û
darvedan e, biyê dê me weha ye.
 
In the village right now it's only this, looking after
sheep. And tilling, and plowing, and clearing tree roots,
our situation is like this.

115
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:06,000
Çandiniya darê we ye. Naka wextê çandiniyê darê şitlan û
daran ê diçînin dar...
 
It is planting your trees. Right now it's the time for
planting trees and saplings, they plant trees...

116
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:18,000
Kî kar giştekî kar bike em bi nîşandin... çawa kar dikin?
 
Who does all the work, let's show... how do you work?

117
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:22,000
Bi giştî we çend kar dikin di gund da?
 
In general, how many do you work in the village?

118
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:29,000
Wê çend di gund da vê karî dikin? Deh-panzdeh mêr e hene
dîsa... evan...
 
How many in the village do this work? There are ten-fifteen
men again... these...

119
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Deh-panzdeh mêr e hene, ev karî dikin. Înan niha ewa...
eyy... î karê diki... hevine. Deh-panzdeh mêr e, em hene, em
vê karî dikin. Marê, cût tarê dikin.
 
There are ten-fifteen men, they do this work. The ones right
now they... uh... the work they do... there are. We are ten-
fifteen men, we do this work. Tilling, plowing, farming.

120
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Zehmet e an ne zehmet e?
 
Is it difficult or not difficult?

121
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Karê çêtin e, karê tev û çetin ê iştê em kurd in tim karî
cefayê... em dikin. Kurd bo axê watiyê girêdan e.
 
It is tough work, tough and difficult work, here we are
Kurds, always working hard... we do. Kurds are tied to the
soil and homeland.

122
00:14:48,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Em bi welêt û axê xwe re girêdan. Û giş... însanî qîmetê axê
xwe zanibe, êdî axê da kar bike, û ev jî axa me ye. Cihekê
kal û... kal û ejdadê me.
 
We are tied to our country and land. And all... human value
to know their land, then work in the land, and this too is
our land. A place of our ancestors and... our grandfathers
and ancestors.

123
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Pêşiyê me ye, em... em... di axê da xwe re girêdayî ne. Em
pir ji axê hez dikin.
 
It's our ancestors, we... we... are tied to our land. We
love our land very much.

124
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Ka hinekî di wî karî de alîkar bim. Ka. Ji kerema te bêhna
xwe vedî em dest pê bikin.
 
Let me help a little in that work. Let's see. Please, rest a
bit, let's start.

125
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,000
Çawa, wusa dikin?
 
How, do they do it like this?

126
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:18,000
Aha, aha.
 
Yeah, yeah.

127
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:25,000
Sere pûş da ke.
 
Put it on the dry grass.

128
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,000
Gelek em bi hev ra ne.
 
We are a lot together.

129
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:37,000
Gelek bi hev ra ne, eza... tişkî arîca dikim...
 
We are a lot together, I... I am asking for something...

130
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Hûn xwedan in li vî karkirinê.
 
You are owners of doing this work.

131
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:58,000
Em xwedan in xwediyê kar kirine. Ê pir em xwedanê erdê ne. E
xwediyê vê erdê ne... e xwediyê me... erdê ne.
 
We are owners of doing the work. The most we are owners of
the land. The owner of this land is... the owner of us... is
the land.

132
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:05,000
Karekî xweş e. Karê axê karekî ee... ev e... miletî kurd tim
û tim ee...
 
It is nice work. Work of the land is a work uh... this is
it... the Kurdish nation always and always uh...

133
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Bi naliyê na axê e.
 
They are connected to the land.

134
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:15,000
Em tim girêdayî bi axê va ne.
 
We are always connected to the land.

135
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,000
Kevir pir in ne vir?
 
Are there many stones here?

136
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:21,000
Pir kevir pir in, iştê vêra dibên çiyayê Hawarê. Çiyayê
Hawarê ye.
 
Very many stones are there, here they call this Mount Hawar.
It's Mount Hawar.

137
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:24,000
Mala we ava be. Spas ji we re, karekî baş e.
 
Bless you. Thank you, it's good work.

138
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:29,000
Demê me tenê em navbera... em e zêdekî we da alîkar bim a.
Spas ji we re.
 
Our time is only that we between... I would have helped you
more. Thank you.

139
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:44,000
Sağ be. Spas ji te re. Xatirê we. Silametî ji we re, gûla...
gûl ser serê me. Rênimayî û we... û rohnahî û xizmetkariya
we, spas jî we dikin. Bi serketina kurdan, ya rebî.
 
Be healthy. Thank you. Goodbye. Health to you, a flower... a
flower upon our heads. Your guidance and your... and your
light and your service, we thank you too. With the success
of the Kurds, oh Lord.

140
00:16:44,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Spas ji te re, saet xweş.
 
Thank you, have a good time.

141
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Gundî di dawiya zivistanê û destpêka biharê de derdora darên
xwe dikolin, marê dikin û dajon.
 
In late winter and early spring, villagers dig around their
trees, till them and plow them.

142
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:20,000
Dibistanek seretayî jî li gund heye, û zarokên gund heya
refa şeşê tê de dixwînin.
 
There is also a primary school in the village, and the
village children study in it until the sixth grade.

143
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:40,000
Guvaşgeheke kevnar ya zeytûnan jî di gund de hebû. Lê niha
ew xirab bûye. Tê gotin ku zeyta ji vê guvaşgehê derdiket,
ji ya guvaşgehên modern a niha xweştir bû.
 
There was also an ancient olive press in the village. But
now it is ruined. It is said that the oil coming out of this
press was better than that of today's modern presses.

144
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:50,000
Fethî, te dar çêkirî, dara malbata te çêkirî ye.
 
Fethi, you made a tree, you made a family tree.

145
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,000
Te kengî dest pê kir?
 
When did you start?

146
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:57,000
Me di hiştê, salê didawsiye. Du hezar û sêzdeh da da
çêkirîye.
 
We left it, in the year two thousand and three. It was made
in two thousand and thirteen.

147
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:01,000
E, te çawa pê fikirî ye? Hinekî bi terê...
 
Yes, how did you think of it? A little bit about...

148
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Welleh dest pêkê min heye, û şebekî din li gund heye,
pismamê min e, û pismamê min ê, fikra avana bi îtîbar aîle
yek e. Em gişt bavik in a...
 
Well, I started it, and there is another youth in the
village, he's my cousin, and my cousin, the idea of these by
consideration is one family. We are all one lineage...

149
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Fikra me ev bû, em rûniştin bin go ka, em gişt bavik in heta
ka em nava kom kin, bi cemaînan, û em dorek malbatê çêkin.
 
Our idea was this, we sat down and said since we are all one
lineage, let's gather the names, by society, and make a
family tree.

150
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:29,000
Min go a, ez ê ji we re çêkim. Bi îtîbar a ew resm e dirav,
çi tişkî ji dest min tê der. Min go ez ê çêkim. Merivê wi
dest pê kir. Navî... ji da...
 
I said yes, I will make it for you. Considering that
drawing, money, whatever comes from my hand. I said I will
make it. That person started. The name... from...

151
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Ji dapîrê dest pê kirin hat xwarê, heta em gihîştin vî nava.
Vana em kî çû kom kirin. Nav... hinek navî di tiştekî de,
piçûk kom dibin. Nav jî wisa... piçûk dest pê bûn yek dudiya
çêbûn a wisa dest pê kir. Em qenc çêbû kom.
 
Started from the grandmother and came down, until we reached
this name. We collected these small ones. Name... some names
in a thing, small ones get collected. Names also like
that... small ones started, one two were made and like that
it started. It turned out well collected.

152
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Heta xilas bû, ê ku yek rojî dîsa tê da heye, navî wî tê de
heye. Ê mirî ye, heta ê yek rojî. Emrê wî yek rojî be. Me
dîsa nivîsand e.
 
Until it was finished, the one who is one day old is again
in it, his name is in it. The one who is dead, up to the one
day old. Even if his age is one day. We still wrote it.

153
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:12,000
Me dîsa tarîx çêkir, serî, me go her salekî, ev du salî, du
salên pêşîn da, em kanibin lê zêde bikin. Yanî evên taze tên
dinê.
 
We made a date again, the beginning, we said every year,
these two years, the first two years, we can add to it. That
is, these newly born.

154
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:16,000
Ê nava fetha te de du hezar û çardeh da dawî kirî ye?
 
And the names you made until two thousand and fourteen are
finished?

155
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:22,000
Di heman de da te wê nivîsandî ye. Pîştî wî de du sal derbas
bûn e. Te ev tîşt te nû ne nivîsandine.
 
At the same time you wrote it. Two years have passed since
then. You haven't written these new ones.

156
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:28,000
Na me hêjî nenivîsandin e. Bes me nav yen we kom kirin ê li
cem xwe. Gerek ez lê bikim...
 
No, we haven't written them yet. But we have collected your
names with us. I need to add to it...

157
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:33,000
...tişkî weha min az wê de îlawe bikim. Û vî navî ez tekrar,
ez we zêde bikim.
 
...something like this I will add to it. And I will
repeatedly add these names.

158
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:37,000
Tu çûyî kû derê gund û te ev navên hanê derxistin?
 
Where did you go in the village and get these names?

159
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:50,000
Li Şêx e. Em her malekî em difikirin, bi telefonê em hev û
din ra dipirsin heta gihîştin berî. Em pirs dikin navan re,
gihîştin bi wî barî wisa. Em pirsan weha weha heta ku bi wî
barî weha derketî...
 
It is in Şêx. We think of each house, we ask each other on
the phone until we reached the beginning. We ask about the
names, until it reached this degree like this. We asked like
this and like this until it came out like this...

160
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:55,000
Ev Şêx Eyîs a bi aslê kûderê ye. Ji kûder hatine, e... ev
gund e?
 
This Sheikh Eyis, where is his origin. Where did they come
from... this village?

161
00:19:55,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Şêx Eyîs li kûder heye, pismamê me ye. Me bi raste... navê
jî cem wî heye...
 
Where Sheikh Eyis is, he is our cousin. We actually... he
has the name with him too...

162
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,000
nîşan bidin...
 
show...

163
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:08,000
Em gihîştin hate Şêx Cabir, ji we ra nîşan bidin ku ez
dizanim.
 
We have reached Sheikh Cabir, let us show you what I know.

164
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,000
Em gihîştin Şêx Cabir.
 
We have reached Sheikh Cabir.

165
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Mala te ava be, ehlen we sehlen. Bi hatina we...
 
Bless you, welcome. With your arrival...

166
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Belê em derbasî mala Şêx Hisên bûn.
 
Yes, we entered Sheikh Hisen's house.

167
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:18,000
Ev ode, odê Zikirê ye, miletê vî gundî di vê odê da zikir
dibe.
 
This room is the Zikir room, the people of this village
perform zikir in this room.

168
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:22,000
Naha jî gelek gundî bi me ra derbas bûn em spasîya wan
dikin.
 
Now many villagers have come in with us, we thank them.

169
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:25,000
Şêx Mihyedîn em ê ji we pirsin...
 
Sheikh Mihyedin, we will ask you...

170
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:29,000
Ehlen we sehlen ser serê me ser çavên me.
 
Welcome, you are upon our heads and eyes.

171
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Sax bî yabo...
 
Bless you uncle...

172
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:34,000
Ehlen we sehlen ji qenata we ra.
 
Welcome to your channel.

173
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:37,000
Destê we sax bin, hûn ji kengî da li vir zikir dibin?
 
Bless your hands, since when do you perform zikir here?

174
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:45,000
Welle, berî vê fetrê, ku em li gund bûn, gundê me yê jêr, em
zikir dibûn.
 
Well, before this period, when we were in the village, our
lower village, we used to perform zikir.

175
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:50,000
Li mala Şêxoyê Şêx Ebdî, navê kalê me Şêx Ebdî bû, bavikê me
Şêxo bû.
 
In Sheikh Abdi's Sheikh's house, our grandfather's name was
Sheikh Abdi, our father was Sheikho.

176
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:54,000
Û ha ev jî mala Şêx Hisên, lawê Şêx Mihemed e.
 
And this here is Sheikh Hisen's house, son of Sheikh
Mihemed.

177
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:59,000
Bi lexem jî vir da digotin, Kûtê... Kûtê Salih e.
 
They also called him by a nickname here, Kute... Kute Salih.

178
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:04,000
Ha ev jî apê me ye mala pismamê me ye, em gund giştk Şêxler
in.
 
And this is our uncle, our cousin's house, we are all
Sheikhs in the village.

179
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:08,000
Ji gundî Şêx Ehmo ne, kesekî xerîb di me da ti nîne di nav
gundê me da.
 
We are from the village of Sheikh Ehmo, there is no stranger
among us in our village.

180
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:11,000
An go pismam in hevin an qîçkê apê hev in.
 
They are either cousins or uncles' daughters.

181
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:15,000
Berî wê we li kû derê zikir dibûn?
 
Before that, where did you perform zikir?

182
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:18,000
Berî wê em li mala Şêx Ebdî zikir dibûn. Kolê Şêx Ebdî ya.
 
Before that, we performed zikir in Sheikh Abdi's house.
Sheikh Abdi's hut.

183
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,000
Wê demê kî dihatine vir?
 
Who used to come here back then?

184
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:24,000
Em nedihatin vir da qet şebab giştk dihatin li vir zikir
dibûn.
 
We didn't come here, the youth all came here and performed
zikir.

185
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:29,000
Roja pênçşemê, êvarî, înê... em zikir dibûn.
 
On Thursday, in the evening, on Friday... we performed
zikir.

186
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:35,000
Çi qanxweşek, derd hebe dihatin cem me, em zikir dikirin.
 
Whatever sick person or ailment there was, they came to us,
we performed zikir.

187
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:40,000
Ser da em dixwendin, der dikirin, dîn hebe dihatin cem me,
em mist didan.
 
We read over them, cast it out, if there was a crazy person
they came to us, we grabbed them.

188
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:45,000
Em ser da dixwendin, em ban wî ca qo dera dikirin.
 
We read over them, we called upon them and cast it out.

189
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:51,000
Ê qîçkê wan xuetine ten, ceh me haw ji elhamdulîlah xwedê
bîr yabo din rehet dibin.
 
The little girls who were bound came to us, and thank God,
God paved the way and they got well.

190
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:54,000
Rehet dibûn û der dibûn.
 
They got well and it went away.

191
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:58,000
Em giştik jî pismamê hev in, kesî xerîb di me da ti nîne.
 
We are all cousins, there is no stranger among us.

192
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,000
Mezinê we kî bûn, rûspîyê we berê kî bûn?
 
Who were your elders, who were your wise men in the past?

193
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:07,000
Berê giştka kalê Şêx Ehmo bû, di pey kalê Şêx Ehmo ra, kalê
me Şêx Ebdî bû.
 
In the past, the eldest of all was grandfather Sheikh Ehmo,
after grandfather Sheikh Ehmo, it was our grandfather Sheikh
Abdi.

194
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:12,000
Şêx Ebdî evra de gotin Şêx Ebdiyê Kole.
 
Sheikh Abdi, they called him Sheikh Abdi the Hut.

195
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:17,000
Hav mezinê me bûn, ta berekê gindo jî sê birek bûn.
 
These were our elders, there were up to three brothers in
the village.

196
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:20,000
Çar bûn, pênç bûn... de bi erebî, pênç bûn.
 
There were four, five... let's say in Arabic, there were
five.

197
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:25,000
Pênç birakê xwe bûn, bes ê mezin di tê da Şêx Ebdî xuya
dikir.
 
They were five brothers, but the eldest among them, Sheikh
Abdi, stood out.

198
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:28,000
Sulehetiyê li dera çê dikirin,
 
They made peace there,

199
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:34,000
Çi mişkilk hebo naka gunda, şerek bibo an li hev xistin
çêbibo,
 
Whatever problem there was in the villages, if there was a
fight or a clash,

200
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:39,000
Yanî bariyê namûsê çê biba an dert biba, de ket meselê kihel
kirra, nabê hal neke ro.
 
Meaning if there was a matter of honor or an issue, he would
get into the matter and solve it, he wouldn't leave it
unsolved.

201
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:42,000
Çi qase mişkila heman tiqê di bind de hal dikirin.
 
However many problems there were, they solved them right
there.

202
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:48,000
Naho dên vî ra.. dema wî pêncşemo hative... ci qo kas vî der
ceviyane?
 
Now they come here... when Thursday comes... how many people
gather here?

203
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:53,000
Hesab va ro tije debe. Uda nakhno jî shto waxto shoxle.
 
Consider this place gets full. And now it's also a time of
work.

204
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:58,000
Xelk bî shoxla de dardakawa.
 
People are going out to work.

205
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:02,000
I hay rehetneko ware ye, rehetneko ware ye.
 
Whoever isn't relaxed comes, whoever isn't relaxed comes.

206
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:05,000
Roja înê jî mere pirtin.
 
On Friday, we are even more.

207
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:10,000
Çi qase te dabe yo qenato dabe hashe te ho mero ka le ware.
 
As much as you say, the channel will come as many times as
you want.

208
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,000
Em bêt da de bojen.
 
Let's say it more.

209
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:16,000
Am bêt da dabejen, madho dabejen.
 
We say it more, we recite praises.

210
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:20,000
Em bo olya o ashabo ca qosa awa hane am ban giştk dekin.
 
We call upon the saints and companions as many of them as
there are, we call upon them all.

211
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:24,000
O we dere ev sha ji je mayo am daben sabab jo khode ye.
 
And there, this thing is from us, we say the reason is from
God.

212
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:27,000
O dara shto ishê khode orto ne.
 
And there, it is God's work in the middle.

213
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:30,000
Naho am e ca jo bipesan?
 
Now what shall we see?

214
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:35,000
Nakna shabab ke lê xî, mamdihi kî lê xên zikr kan zeve ro.
 
Let the youth play, let them play praises and perform zikir
for you.

215
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:40,000
Jo ve milleti ro, bî bînin shto am shekhlar in am jo gondî
shekh hmuna.
 
For this people, to see that we are Sheikhs, we are from
Sheikh Hmun's village.

216
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:45,000
Jo cad o bav o kalo mada am shekhlar in.
 
From our ancestors and grandfathers, we are Sheikhs.

217
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:50,000
Jo ch qosa l’em qazo nizanin po show ro dagotin shekhler.
 
As much as they don't know, from the past they called us
Sheikhs.

218
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:54,000
Kalo aslaf ji hati dogotin do we galo do.
 
Grandfather Aslaf also came and said in that valley.

219
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:57,000
G’waqte do wa cawro em zanin shakhlar biko.
 
At that time, we knew we were Sheikhs.

220
00:24:57,000 --> 00:25:00,000
Çelolar kever kî tul kire nav shoqe o nadidan.
 
They made a wall of stones, extended it inside the gorge and
didn't show it.

221
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:05,000
Wo jeno jeno l’pêsh vo ja heya g’wa ca shoqolar va ja jo va
gari.
 
And there is a place in front where that gorge is.

222
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:09,000
Wo ca got go hove tesh nobe shekh a.
 
He said there that nothing else but Sheikh.

223
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:14,000
Yani jo wa assasda am shekhlar in a am zanin am shakhlar ina
wa elhamdulillah. Am biche g’babe.
 
Meaning from that foundation we are Sheikhs, we know we are
Sheikhs, and thank God. We are whatever may be.

224
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:18,000
Khode kemasî wa nede. Na jo am bî peshan ke dosbke beje?
 
May God not give you shortcomings. Now let's see, who will
start to say it?

225
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:22,000
Shekh Henan o bito beje.
 
Sheikh Henan will start to say it.

226
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:35,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

227
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:46,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

228
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Ez ban dikim ya Mihemed, Seyid ya mamda hê
 
I call upon oh Muhammad, Sayyid, oh I praise.

229
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:58,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

230
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:06,000
Ez ban dikim Ebdil Qadir, Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I call upon Abdul Qadir, lion of Allah, I praise.

231
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:12,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

232
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:20,000
Ez ban dikim ya Rîfaî, Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I call upon oh Rifai, lion of Allah, I praise.

233
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:26,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

234
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:33,000
Ez ban dikim ya Bedewî, Seyîd ya mamda hê
 
I call upon oh Badawi, Sayyid, oh I praise.

235
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:39,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

236
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:46,000
Ez ban dikim ya Desûqî, Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I call upon oh Dasuqi, lion of Allah, I praise.

237
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:51,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

238
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:58,000
Ez ban dikim ya Şêx Selîm, Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I call upon oh Sheikh Selim, lion of Allah, I praise.

239
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:05,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

240
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:11,000
Ez ban dikim El-Xeybûr, Seyîd ya mamda hê
 
I call upon Al-Khabur, Sayyid, oh I praise.

241
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:17,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

242
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:23,000
Ez ban dikim Ezeddîno, Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I call upon Izz al-Din, lion of Allah, I praise.

243
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:29,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

244
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:36,000
Ez ban dikim Mhiyedîno, Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I call upon Muhyi al-Din, lion of Allah, I praise.

245
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:42,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

246
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:49,000
Ez ban dikim Tacedîno, Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I call upon Taj al-Din, lion of Allah, I praise.

247
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:55,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

248
00:27:55,000 --> 00:28:02,000
Ez ban dikim Henan Menan, Seyîd ya mamda hê
 
I call upon Hanan Manan, Sayyid, oh I praise.

249
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:08,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

250
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:15,000
Ez ban dikim Dêyan Burhan, Seyîd ya mamda hê
 
I call upon Deyan Burhan, Sayyid, oh I praise.

251
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:21,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

252
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:28,000
Ez ban dikim Sîno Seydo, Siltan ya mamda hê
 
I call upon Sino Seydo, Sultan, oh I praise.

253
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:34,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

254
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:41,000
Ez ban dikim Bobê Lawe, Siltan ya mamda hê
 
I call upon Bobe Lawe, Sultan, oh I praise.

255
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:46,000
Mamda hêm mamda hê Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I praise, I praise, lion of Allah, I praise.

256
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:56,000
Ez ban dikim Qûmaş ê Xar, Şêrê Allah mamda hê
 
I call upon Qumash the Crooked, lion of Allah, I praise.

257
00:28:56,000 --> 00:29:00,000
Gundê Şêx girêdayî navçeya Recoyê ye, Kantona Efrînê dikeve.
 
Sheikh village is connected to the Reco district, located in
the Afrin Canton.

258
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:04,000
Bîst û pênc kîlometreyî, li rojavayê wajaroka Reco
 
Twenty-five kilometers to the west of the town of Reco

259
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:08,000
Û sîh kîlometreyî li bakurê bajarê Efrînê dikeve.
 
And it is located thirty kilometers north of the city of
Afrin.

260
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:12,000
Dema te yê amavê gundê Şêx da xuyadibe
 
When you hear the name of Sheikh village, it seems

261
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:16,000
Ku tê da kesên oldar an go Şêx hene.
 
That there are religious people or Sheikhs in it.

262
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:20,000
Lê belê ev gund bi vê taybetmendiyê tê nas kirin
 
But indeed this village is recognized by this characteristic

263
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:27,000
Ji ber ku di nav gundê Şêxan de kur û barên olî yên îslamî,
xwendina Mewlûd û Zikir
 
Because within the Sheikh's village, Islamic religious
affairs, reading of the Mawlid and Zikir

264
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:31,000
Navê gund jî ji navê Eşîra Şêxan hatiye.
 
The name of the village has also come from the name of the
Sheikh tribe.

265
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:35,000
Û niştecihên gund ji şaxekî Eşîra Şêxan e
 
And the residents of the village are from a branch of the
Sheikh tribe

266
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:39,000
Ku bi aliyekî xwesiye, ku ew şaxek jî Rîfaiyê Şêxan e.
 
Which is unique in a way, as that branch is the Rifai of the
Sheikhs.

267
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:44,000
Tê gotin ku ji beriya sedsalan diyarve, kesek bi navê Şêx
Ehmed
 
It is said that apparently hundreds of years ago, a person
named Sheikh Ehmed

268
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:48,000
Ji gundê Daşlûkê, yê Herêma Kobanê hat
 
Came from the village of Dashluk, in the Kobane Region

269
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:53,000
Û li gundê dika, di serî da niştecîh bû.
 
And first settled in the village of Dika.

270
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:57,000
Lê piştî ku zewicî, xaniyek li cihekî din ava kir...
 
But after he got married, he built a house in another
place...

271
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Û ev cih pişt re bû wekî gundekê, bi navê gundê Şêx hat
naskirin.
 
And this place later became like a village, recognized by
the name of Sheikh village.

272
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:11,000
Hêjayî gotinê ye ku malbata Şêx Ehmed û weke şêxên din nas
dikirin û ta niha kevnepişopiyên bav û kalên xwe bernedane û
bi kar tînin.
 
It is worth mentioning that Sheikh Ahmed's family, like
other Sheikhs, were well known and until now they have not
abandoned the traditions of their ancestors and still use
them.

273
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:31,000
Heftane şînê yên gund ji merasîman re amade dibin. Û herwiha
li ser cenazeyên miriyên xwe jî, bi merasîmên olî miriyê xwe
radikin.
 
Every week, the elders of the village prepare for the
ceremonies. And also at the funerals of their dead, they
bury their dead with religious ceremonies.

274
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,000
Merheba xwîşkê.
 
Hello, sister.

275
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,000
Ehlen wesahlen.
 
Welcome.

276
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:34,000
Destên we sax bin.
 
Bless your hands.

277
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:39,000
Destên we jî sax bin. Xwedê we rabike, ser çavan, hûn hatin
bi xêr hatin, ehlen wesahlen.
 
Bless your hands too. May God elevate you, upon my eyes, you
have come, welcome.

278
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:43,000
Spas xwîşkê. Destê te wî hemiyan xweş bin.
 
Thank you, sister. Bless all your hands.

279
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:51,000
We jî hinek tiştên xwarinên Kurdan we amade kiriye. Dayê ka
ji me re navê xwarinên xwe bêje, te çi amade kiriye û çi?
 
You have also prepared some Kurdish food. Mother, tell us
the names of your foods, what have you prepared and what?

280
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:58,000
Em îro Kerdî çêdikin. Me Kerdî anî şûşt. Em ê hûr bikin.
Pîvaz jî me hûr kirin.
 
We are making Kerdi today. We brought Kerdi and washed it.
We will chop it. We also chopped the onions.

281
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:00,000
Em ê biqelînin.
 
We will fry them.

282
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:06,000
Em ê xwêya xwe têkin, lehmecûna têkin, ew ê rind bikelînin,
biqelînin.
 
We will add our salt, add meat, it will boil well, fry.

283
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:13,000
Em ê paşê jî bulxuriya xwe têkin û paşê jî em ê tirşiya xwe
têkin, em ê bikelînin. Bikelînin û deynin.
 
We will then add our bulgur and then we will add our
sourness, we will boil it. Boil it and put it aside.

284
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:15,000
Yanî destpêkê hûn ê biqelînin?
 
So first you will fry it?

285
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:18,000
Erê. Piştî wê tê qelandin, tê kelandin.
 
Yes. After it is fried, it is boiled.

286
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:21,000
Ev li gund dibe?
 
Is this found in the village?

287
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:28,000
Erê, erê li gund dibe li çiyê.
 
Yes, yes, it grows in the village on the mountain.

288
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:33,000
Naha dema pincarê jî, ka em tiştekî bipirsin... Dema pincarê
hûn di wê demê de çi pincarê çêdikin?
 
Now during the time of herbs, let's ask something... During
the time of herbs, what herbs do you prepare?

289
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:40,000
Nanê qûtikê. Darsongk, sîrik, kerbeng, şivîk, meze, ev em
tînin... pak dişon û em hûr dikin.
 
Qutik bread. Darsongk, sirik, kerbeng, shivik, meze, we
bring these... wash them clean and we chop them.

290
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:45,000
Pîvazê xwe diqelînin, pincarê xwe çêdikin ser û em dixwin.
 
We fry our onions, put our herbs on top and we eat.

291
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,000
Ev bi taybetî di kîjan mehê de peyda dibin?
 
In which month are these specifically found?

292
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:53,000
Ev di meha duduyan de peyda dibe, yanî meha duduyan de dest
pê dike heta meha çaran.
 
These are found in the second month, so it starts in the
second month until the fourth month.

293
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:59,000
Meha çaran qert dibe. Nika taze ye em çêdikin dixwin. Carna
dereng dibare, sal dereng dibare.
 
In the fourth month it becomes tough. Now it's fresh, we
make it and eat it. Sometimes it rains late, the year rains
late.

294
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:04,000
Darê meha yekê dibare, carna meha duduyan dibare.
 
The trees bloom in the first month, sometimes in the second
month.

295
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:07,000
Ka em hinek tiştên din jî bipirsin. Ev Kerdî li kû derê bi
taybetî dibe?
 
Let's ask some other things. Where does this Kerdi
specifically grow?

296
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:11,000
Li gundan dibe. Li çolê dibe, nav keleman dibe.
 
It grows in the villages. It grows in the wild, among the
thorns.

297
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:12,000
Yanî ev deştan dibe yan jî çiya dibe?
 
So it grows in the plains or in the mountains?

298
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:18,000
Erê, deştan jî dibe û çiya jî dibe. Û min pir dît li
Selimiyê, yanî ne tenê li cem Kurdan heye.
 
Yes, it grows in the plains and also in the mountains. And I
saw a lot in Salamiyah, so it's not only among Kurds.

299
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:24,000
Li cem ereban jî heye. Carna em çûn, ereban bi navê xwe Lûf
e.
 
It is also among Arabs. Sometimes we went, Arabs call it by
its name Luf.

300
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:30,000
Û li Dêrikê jî hebû. Min dît ku kirine tirş û me xwar. Û bi
rastî jî dibêjin Lûf çêdikin.
 
And it was also in Derik. I saw that they made it sour and
we ate it. And really they say they make Luf.

301
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:34,000
Dibêjin fêdeya xwe ji tenduristiyê re, ji me'deyê re pir
heye.
 
They say it has many benefits for health, for the stomach.

302
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:40,000
Û ji nexweşiya penceşêrê re jî dibêjin fêde ye. Û heta kurmê
zik derdixe.
 
And they also say it is beneficial for cancer. And it even
expels stomach worms.

303
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:50,000
Ên ku kurm hene derdixe. Û şehiyê mirov jî vedike, tu
dixwazî nan pir bixwî. Ev in ku ji bo tenduristiyê dixwin.
 
Those who have worms, it expels them. And it also opens up a
person's appetite, you want to eat a lot of bread. These are
what they eat for health.

304
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:55,000
Min tiştekî din jî bihîstibû, dibêjin... ez nizanim bê ka
xwarina wî çawa dikin... ew zehîr e?
 
I had also heard another thing, they say... I don't know how
they eat it... is it poison?

305
00:32:55,000 --> 00:33:00,000
Erê... Bixwe zehîr e. Bi tirşê, tê kelandin û bi tirşê...
 
Yes... It is poison itself. With sourness, it is boiled and
with sourness...

306
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:04,000
Tirşê simaqê tê kelandin, ew zehîr wî jê diçe.
 
Sour sumac is boiled, its poison goes away.

307
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:11,000
Heger wek bixwî, devê te giş biwerime û tu nikarî... yanî
heta tu hûr jî bikî destê te dişaweşîne.
 
If you eat it like that, your whole mouth will swell and you
can't... I mean, even if you just chop it, it makes your
hands sting.

308
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:12,000
Zehîr e?
 
It's poison?

309
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:16,000
Zehîr e. Belê. Bes fêdeya xwe jî pir heye.
 
It's poison. Yes. But it also has many benefits.

310
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,000
Yanî destpêkê hûn vî zehîrî jê dikişînin?
 
So first you extract this poison from it?

311
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:22,000
Erê. Paşê tu dikelînî. Heta Ermenî jî dikelînin, dixwin.
 
Yes. Then you boil it. Even Armenians boil it and eat it.

312
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:30,000
Salê sê çar cara dibêjin, heq e em bixwin vî. Ermenî li
Heleb... cîranên me bûn, ew jî çêdikirin.
 
Three or four times a year they say, it's our right to eat
this. Armenians in Aleppo... they were our neighbors, they
also made it.

313
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,000
Çawa dikirin?
 
How did they make it?

314
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:33,000
Wan jî wek me çêdikirin. Lê me hinekî cuda çêdikir...
 
They also made it like us. But we made it a bit
differently...

315
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:39,000
Na, te behsa Dêrikê kir û te behsa Selimiyê kir û te behsa
Helebê kir. Hemî bi giştî wek hev çêdikin?
 
No, you mentioned Derik and you mentioned Salamiyah and you
mentioned Aleppo. Do they all make it the same way
generally?

316
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:45,000
Giştî wek hev... Bes hin hene bilxur nakinê. Tirşê û xalî
çêdikin.
 
Generally the same... But some don't add bulgur. They make
it with sourness and alone.

317
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:49,000
Û hin hene dikinê. Ê Selimiyê nedikirinê.
 
And some do add it. Those in Salamiyah did not add it.

318
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:52,000
Ê Dêrikê nedikirinê. Ermenî nedikirinê.
 
Those in Derik did not add it. Armenians did not add it.

319
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:57,000
Bes me bilxur dikirê, em kurmanc bilxur dikinê. Û wilo.
 
But we added bulgur, we Kurds add bulgur. And like that.

320
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:00,000
Li kîjan deveran, ev li Selimiyê û li Dêrikê dibe, li kîjan
cihan dibe?
 
In which areas, in Salamiyah and Derik, in what places does
it grow?

321
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:07,000
Her cihê ku av lê heye dibe, cihê ku şilî tê da hebe dibe.
 
Everywhere there is water it grows, a place that is wet it
grows.

322
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:14,000
Yanî lê belê li deştê jî dibe. Li çiyê jî dibe, li nav
keleman da jî dibe.
 
So it also grows in the plains. It grows in the mountains
too, among the thorns.

323
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Li Selimiyê bi gelemperî li nav baxçeyan dibe... Lê her cihî
hene.
 
In Salamiyah mostly in gardens... But it's everywhere.

324
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:22,000
Di kîjan mehê de ev te got peyda dibe, yanî dest pê dike?
 
In which month did you say it appears, or starts?

325
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:28,000
Meha duduya dest pê dike... heta meha çaran xelas dibe. Heta
meha çaran qert dibe.
 
It starts in the second month... until the fourth month it
finishes. By the fourth month it becomes tough.

326
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:36,000
Heta wextê bihara dereng dibe, ew hişk dibe wek darê genim.
Em jê re dibêjin hişk dibe.
 
Even when spring comes late, it dries up like wheat stalks.
We say it dries up.

327
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:49,000
Hinek ji wan wek sêvê vedibe. Carna ew jî dikin xwarin,
dibêjin ji bo tenduristiyê baş e.
 
Some of them open up like an apple. Sometimes they cook that
too, they say it's good for health.

328
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:50,000
Ew fêdeya wê çiye?
 
What is its benefit?

329
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:58,000
Ji bo me'dê, ew me'deya ku gellek xirab e, xelibî ye. Tê
zanîn ku fêde dike, û ji bo hezmê jî baş e.
 
For the stomach, for a very bad stomach, it is upset. It is
known to be beneficial, and it's also good for digestion.

330
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,000
Û şehiyê mirov jî vedike, tu dixwazî nan bixwî.
 
And it opens up a person's appetite, you want to eat bread.

331
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:05,000
Û kurmê zik derdixe û dibêjin ji penceşêrê re jî baş e.
 
And it expels stomach worms and they say it's also good for
cancer.

332
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:13,000
Baş e. Tiştekî din jî em dipirsin. Ev tiştên xwarinên ku hûn
amade dikin... te got navê wê çiye?
 
Okay. We ask another thing. These foods that you are
preparing... what did you say its name was?

333
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:18,000
Navê avan te got. Ev em jê re dibêjin...
 
You said the name of these. We call this...

334
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:19,000
Ev we çi amade kiriye?
 
What have you prepared here?

335
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:21,000
Em me tiştek din çêkiriye.
 
We have made another thing.

336
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:27,000
Wê jî em piştre bînin we çawa amade kiriye. Ka behsa wê bike
da ku em bizanin we çawa çêkiriye.
 
We will bring it later, how you prepared it. Tell us about
it so we know how you made it.

337
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:33,000
Ev semîtek bulxureke hûr e, nerm e. Em çêdikin, em tînin
pîvaz û bacan û îsot û giya dikinê, paşê ziwa hûr dikin tê
de.
 
This is semit, a fine, soft bulgur. We make it, we bring
onions and tomatoes and peppers and herbs, then we chop them
dry in it.

338
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:40,000
Çi tişt hebe em dikin... em tînin hişîniyan hûr dikin yê
taze, îsota xwe diqelînin, em avê didinê.
 
Whatever we have, we add... we bring fresh greens and chop
them, fry our pepper, we add water to it.

339
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:47,000
Bulxurê xwe nerm dikin, em zeyta xwe dikinê û paşê hişîniyê
nav dikin. Û paşê wek hûr dibe em têdixin. Gellekî xweş
dibe.
 
We soften our bulgur, we put our oil in and then mix the
greens. And then when it is chopped we add it. It becomes
very delicious.

340
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:52,000
We berê yek jî amade kiriye, hûn çi amade bikin ev çi ye? Ev
we çawa çêkiriye?
 
You prepared one earlier too, what are you preparing, what
is this? How did you make this?

341
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:54,000
Ev jî şilik e.
 
This is also shilik.

342
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:56,000
Ew ka çawa çêdikin?
 
How is that made?

343
00:35:56,000 --> 00:36:05,000
Şilik, em hevîr distirên wek normal. Nan em çêdikin û paşê
jî em di nav rûn de sor dikin, wek li ser sêlê amade dikin.
 
Shilik, we knead dough like normal. We make bread and then
we fry it in oil, prepare it like on a saje (metal plate).

344
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:14,000
Û me paşê şerbet kela ye. Û wisa me amade kiriye. Em datînin
ser hev, em ê ji xwe re bixwin.
 
And then we boiled syrup. And we prepared it like that. We
stack them on top of each other, we will eat it.

345
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:23,000
Ev wek şîraniyekê ye... hûn gelek şîraniyên din jî amade
dikin. Ev çi ye? Te navê wan negot?
 
This is like a dessert... you also prepare many other
desserts. What are these? Didn't you say their names?

346
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:25,000
Ev hejîrok in.
 
These are hejirok (fig sweets).

347
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,000
Ka çawa çêdikin hûn vê?
 
How do you make these?

348
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:33,000
Hejîrok em dikelînin... em dikin şerbetê û em dikelînin...
heta ku ew xweş dibin, nerm dibin.
 
We boil hejirok... we put them in syrup and we boil them...
until they become nice, they become soft.

349
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:44,000
Em semîtê tevlî dikin... em gûz û behîv û fistiqan gişt hûr
dikin. Me zeyt... carna em dimsê jî tê dikin em dikelînin.
 
We mix in sesame seeds... we chop walnuts and almonds and
pistachios. We put oil... sometimes we add molasses too, we
boil it.

350
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:50,000
Me çêkir paşê wek em hûr kirin datînin.
 
We made it then we put it down like we chopped them.

351
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:53,000
Em didin hevdu wek didin qatên xwarê. Û em wan paşê
diqetînin.
 
We put them together like stacking layers down. And then we
cut them.

352
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,000
Ev heta çendekê dimînin?
 
How long do these stay?

353
00:36:54,000 --> 00:37:01,000
Dibe heşt rojan, deh rojan dudu rojan. Ev jî dem e. Da ku
xweşik bibin wek tu sabrê xwe pê tînî.
 
Maybe eight days, ten days or two days. This is also a time.
So they become nice, as you are patient with them.

354
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:05,000
Zivistanan jî em sabrê xwe pê tînin.
 
In winter we are also patient with it (snack on it).

355
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:08,000
Destên we sax bin dayê. Ka em dest pê bikin.
 
Bless your hands, mother. Let's begin.

356
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:15,000
Em Kerdî hûr dikin û em wî diqelînin. Em tirşîyê xwe jî
dikinê, lehmecûn jî tê dikin.
 
We chop the Kerdi and we fry it. We also add our sourness,
put meat in it too.

357
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:24,000
Rûnê xwe jî em dikinê. Û em bulxura xwe jî dikinê... û em
tirşiya xwe dikinê. Em dikelînin û dûre em datînin.
 
We put our oil in. And we also put our bulgur... and we put
our sourness. We boil it and then we set it down.

358
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:30,000
Te zanî xwarina gunda wisa pirrî tamxweş e. Tu qet nabêjî li
bajaran... wisa bajarokan...
 
You know village food is very delicious. You don't even say
in cities... like towns...

359
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:31,000
Na...
 
No...

360
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,000
Tu bajar jî naxwazî?
 
You don't even like the city?

361
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:38,000
Na, ez naxwazim ez naçim. Min xwarina gundan ez pir
dixwazim.
 
No, I don't want to, I don't go. I want village food a lot.

362
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:40,000
Bes a bajar te tiştek nexwariye?
 
But you haven't eaten anything in the city?

363
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:46,000
Min nexwariye gellek. Ne pirrî zêde.
 
I haven't eaten much. Not very much.

364
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:47,000
Tu wek tiştek dibînî xwarina bajaran?
 
Do you see city food as something special?

365
00:37:47,000 --> 00:38:00,000
Na... min ne dît. Me xwarinên gunda pirrî hez kir. Zêde...
min bixwe tam kiriye. Tê bîra me demên borî pir me ew
xwarine.
 
No... I haven't. We liked village food a lot. A lot... I
tasted it myself. We remember the past times, we ate them a
lot.

366
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:20,000
Hêjayî gotinê ye ku hemû Şêxên li Herêma Efrînê dijîn
bîngeha wan ji Kobanê ne.
 
It is worth mentioning that all the Sheikhs living in the
Afrin region have their origins from Kobani.

367
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:34,000
Gelek kes ji gundî biçûk da xwendine. Û xwendina xwe li
bajar û bajarokan berdewam kirine.
 
Many people from the village have studied since they were
little. And they continued their studies in cities and
towns.

368
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:46,000
Ji ber ku xelkê gund gellekî ji xwendinê hez dikin, tê de
xwendinên cuda yên pîşeyî û pisporiyê xwendine. Zanîngeh
qedandine.
 
Because the village people like education very much, they
have studied various professional and specialized fields.
They graduated from universities.

369
00:38:46,000 --> 00:39:00,000
Di civakê de cih girtine û lîstikên xwe wekî peyda kirine û
pêk anîne.
 
They took their place in society and maintained and played
their games.

370
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:12,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja, dê werin em bi hev ra lîstikên gund
jî nas bikin. Gelek lîstikên gund hene, di demên kin da
wenda bûn.
 
Yes dear viewers, come let's get to know the village games
together. There are many village games, they were lost in a
short time.

371
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:17,000
Şêx xwestin em wan lîstikan jî nîşan bikin û wan dîsa dubare
bikin. Dema berê dilîstin. Merheba ciwano.
 
The Sheikhs wanted us to show those games and repeat them
again. They played them in the past. Hello young man.

372
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:24,000
Ehlen wesahlen... Mît seleme... hemû spas ji bo we. Xêr
hatine xaltî û xalo. Ehlen wesahlen.
 
Welcome... A hundred greetings... all thanks to you. Welcome
aunt and uncle. Welcome.

373
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:28,000
Spas ciwano. We behsa lîstikan kir, hûn berê çi dilîstin?
 
Thank you young man. You mentioned the games, what did you
play before?

374
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:35,000
Welleh gellek lîstik me berê dilîst. Lîstika şebabo, qîntê
hebû.
 
By God we played many games before. There was the game of
shababo, qinte.

375
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:44,000
Tûşê hebû. Çogûkê hebû. Me digel lîstikan, bi gund re
dilîstin. Çend kes dilîstin.
 
There was tushe. There was choguke. Along with the games, we
played with the village. Several people played.

376
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:50,000
Pîmpoz hebû. Feqîre hebû. Ceme ew tişt hebin, em dixwazin em
ji xwe zarokatiya xwe dîsa bikin...
 
There was pimpoz. There was feqire. All these things exist,
we want to recreate our childhood for ourselves...

377
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:56,000
Hûn dixwazin em pêşiyê lîstikên gund wisa dilîstin pêk
bînin?
 
You want us first to implement the village games that were
played?

378
00:39:56,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Me amade kiriye ji birayên xwe ra em ê pêk bînin, em ê
lîstikên gund yên berê dîsa nû bikin, daxwazên nû wan
lîstikan em ê li dar bixin.
 
We have prepared for our brothers to implement them, we will
renew the old village games again, new requests to organize
those games.

379
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:05,000
Ev turasê kevin bûn, hinda bûn, em ê derxin ji miletê xwe ra
pêşkêş bikin.
 
These old heritages were lost, we are going to take them out
and present them to our people.

380
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:08,000
Vê lîstika we giringî pê daye, çi lîstik e? Navê wê çi ye?
 
This game that you've given importance to, what game is it?
What is its name?

381
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:15,000
Cûtî kûsî heye, cema'et. Ew jî kevin bû, ew jî hinda bibû di
nav gelê me yê Kurd da.
 
We have the double turtles, folks. This is also old, it was
lost among our Kurdish people too.

382
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,000
Ew çawa tê lîstin?
 
How is it played?

383
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:19,000
Ewa du mêr e, xwe bi hev û din girê didin.
 
Two men tie themselves together.

384
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:24,000
Bi bê pêyê xwe di bin pêyê hev ra derbas dikin. Yek di xwe
da dikşîne, yek di xwe da dikşîne.
 
With their bare feet, they cross their legs under each
other's. One pulls towards himself, the other pulls towards
himself.

385
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:28,000
Kîjanî xalib bûn, ew e cûtî kûsî ye.
 
Whoever wins, that is the double turtles.

386
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:29,000
Ê ya din?
 
And the other one?

387
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:30,000
Ê ya din feq û rovî ye.
 
The other one is the trap and the fox.

388
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:31,000
Ew çawa tê lîstin?
 
How is it played?

389
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:36,000
Ewa destê wî yekê... yek feqê xwe dikin... destê wî girê
didin û lingê wî girê didin.
 
That is, his hand... one becomes the trap... they tie his
hand, and they tie his leg.

390
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:41,000
Yê din jî pê va daliqînin û diqulibînin, dibe feq û rovî, vî
carî nikanin xwe qulipînin.
 
The other one is hooked to him and flipped, it becomes the
trap and the fox, they cannot flip over.

391
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:43,000
Berê gundî bi hemîyan dilîstin?
 
In the past, did the villagers play with all of them?

392
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:48,000
Ewa, piştî karê xwe, yê cotkariya xwe, yê zikiriya
dikirin...
 
Yes, after their work, their farming, their plowing...

393
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:52,000
Yanê derbas dikirin evde şevan, bi vî lîstikana kevin.
 
Meaning they spent these nights, with these old games.

394
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:54,000
Bi taybet xort dilîstin?
 
Did the young men specially play?

395
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:55,000
Tabaen, xort.
 
Of course, the young men.

396
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:56,000
Niha kî ye bilîze?
 
Who will play now?

397
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:58,000
Niha, kurê xwîşka min, Henan.
 
Now, my nephew, Henan.

398
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:00,000
Û yek jî biraziyê min...
 
And also my other nephew...

399
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:03,000
Hekîm. Lawo, pismamê min e.
 
Hekîm. Boy, he's my cousin.

400
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,000
Ka kîjan Henan e? Ev Henan, ev?
 
Which one is Henan? This one is Henan, this one?

401
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,000
Ev Henan e.
 
This is Henan.

402
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,000
Henan û Hekîm, hûn ê bilîzin?
 
Henan and Hekîm, are you going to play?

403
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,000
Em ê, em ê bilîzin.
 
Yes, we are going to play.

404
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:09,000
Berê we cara lîstine? Yan cara yekem e hûn ê bilîzin?
 
Have you ever played it before? Or is this the first time
you're playing?

405
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:10,000
Cara yekem e.
 
It's the first time.

406
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:13,000
Nê te bîr e we, çawa bav û kalên we, bavo we dilîstin we
dîtine?
 
Don't you remember, did you see how your grandfathers and
fathers played?

407
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,000
Ne te bîra min, wile.
 
I don't remember, really.

408
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:16,000
Bes, vî zemanî hûn bilîzin a?
 
But, you are going to play in this time?

409
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:18,000
Em ê bextê xwe... Em ê bextê xwe... Weke çawa tiştin e.
 
We will try our luck... We will try our luck... Like how
things are.

410
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:20,000
Ne zehmet e?
 
Isn't it difficult?

411
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:21,000
Na.
 
No.

412
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,000
Ê kerem ke.
 
Go ahead then.

413
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:23,000
Kî, ez?
 
Who, me?

414
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,000
Na, tê girêdî.
 
Well, will you tie him.

415
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:34,000
Erê. Niha lingê wî û destê wî weha girê didim.
 
Yes. Now I will tie his leg and his hand.

416
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:38,000
Îştê ev feq e. Ev feq û rovî ye.
 
Look, this is the trap. This is the trap and the fox.

417
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,000
Çawa berê rovî dihat dketin feqê yan na...
 
Like how the fox used to fall into the trap in the past...

418
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,000
Ewa, weke wê ye.
 
Yes, like that.

419
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:48,000
Niha lingê wî em ê girê din, destê wî jî girê din, nikare
xwe veke.
 
Now we will tie his leg, and his hand too, he cannot untie
himself.

420
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:50,000
Ka yê din.
 
Where is the other one.

421
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:57,000
Wile raşatê te ne baş e Henan. Xêr e.
 
Really, your luck is not good Henan. May it be well.

422
00:41:57,000 --> 00:42:00,000
Te girêda ha.
 
You tied him.

423
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:03,000
Dest û lingê wî jî girêde, pê va derbas ke.
 
Tie his hand and leg too, pass them through.

424
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:07,000
Pêyê xwe jî, pêyê xwe jî di wî da dîsa ra derbas ke.
 
Your leg too, cross your leg through his again.

425
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:10,000
Pêyê xwe jî. Pêyê xwe jî.
 
Your leg too. Your leg too.

426
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:13,000
Na, te girêk feqê!
 
No, you tie the trap!

427
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,000
Pêyê wî derbas kin di yê te.
 
Pass his leg through yours.

428
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:18,000
Henan hoşa xwe bikşîne.
 
Henan, pull yourself together.

429
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,000
Ê niha çawa dibe?
 
Well, how does it go now?

430
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:20,000
Niha nikanin xwe bifiltînin.
 
Now they cannot escape.

431
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:24,000
Hekîm bû rovî û feqê ket niha nikare xwe bifilitîne?
 
Hekîm became the fox and fell into the trap, now he cannot
escape?

432
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:26,000
Lingê xwe dirêj kin, lingê xwe ana dirêj kin.
 
Stretch out your legs, stretch your legs out like this.

433
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:28,000
Êgeh niha çawa bike dare...
 
How is the game now... he can't get out...

434
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:29,000
Niha derên, eva ye.
 
Now get out, this is it.

435
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:31,000
Eva feq û rovî ye.
 
This is the trap and the fox.

436
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:36,000
Yanê niha heta yek netê destê wan veneke, niha nikanin
bifilitin.
 
Meaning now until someone comes and unties their hands, they
cannot escape now.

437
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:48,000
Wile rewşa we ne baş e.
 
Really, your situation is not good.

438
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:52,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja, piştî lîstika xwe li vir jî em ê
xatirê xwe ji we bixwazin.
 
Yes dear viewers, after our game here we will say goodbye to
you.

439
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:58,000
Li vir em gehiştin dawiya bernameya xwe. Bixatirê we, heya
hefteyeke din em ê dîsa bi hev ra bin.
 
Here we have reached the end of our program. Goodbye, until
next week we will be together again.

440
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:01,000
Heyran û gerdenê zer
 
My dear with the golden neck

